  • Class
    Description
    AddMoodActivity
    AddMoodActivity is responsible for allowing users to add a new mood entry.
    EditEmojiActivity
    EditEmojiActivity allows users to select a new emoji for their mood entry.
    EditEmojiResources
    EditEmojiResources is a utility class that provides methods to retrieve mood-related resources such as colors, descriptions, and drawable resources based on the emoji name.
    EditMoodActivity
    EditMoodActivity allows users to edit an existing mood entry.
    EmojiSelectionActivity
    EmojiSelectionActivity allows users to select an emoji representing their current mood.
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    ExampleUnitTest
    Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
    ForgotPasswordActivity
    ForgotPasswordActivity allows users to reset their password by providing their registered email address.
    ImageHandler
    ImageHandler is a utility class that handles image selection, compression, and uploading to Firebase Storage.
    ImageHandler.OnImageLoadedListener
     
    ImageHandler.OnImageUploadListener
    Listener interface for image upload events.
    LoginActivity
    LoginActivity handles user authentication and login functionality.
    MainActivity
    MainActivity is the main screen of the application where users can view their mood entries.
    Mood
    The Mood class represents a mood entry in the application.
    MoodAdapter
    MoodAdapter is a custom ArrayAdapter for displaying mood entries in a ListView or RecyclerView.
    MoodDataCache
    Singleton cache for storing and managing mood document data.
    MoodDetailActivity
    MoodDetailActivity displays detailed information about a specific mood entry.
    RegisterActivity
    RegisterActivity handles user registration functionality.
    User
    The User class represents a singleton instance of the current user in the application.
